  "prompt": "Is there such a thing as an agnostic theist?",
  "response": "Yes, there is such a concept as an agnostic theist. An agnostic theist is someone who believes in the existence of a god or gods but maintains that the nature or existence of this divine being is unknown or unknowable. Essentially, they have faith in a higher power but acknowledge that they cannot fully understand or prove the existence of that power through empirical means or definitive evidence. This stance combines elements of both agnosticism (uncertainty about the knowledge of the divine) and theism (belief in the divine).",
